black.dockerfile:
# Use the official Python image from the Docker Hub
FROM python:3.12-slim AS builder

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the repository contents into the container
COPY . /app/

# Create a virtual environment and install necessary tools and dependencies
RUN python -m venv /opt/venv
RUN /opt/venv/bin/python -m pip install --no-cache-dir hatch hatch-fancy-pypi-readme hatch-vcs

# Set the virtual environment as the active environment
SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c", ". /opt/venv/bin/activate"]

# Install build tools and build the project
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y build-essential git python3-dev 
RUN hatch build -t wheel

# Create the final lightweight image
FROM python:3.12-slim

# Set the working directory in the final image
WORKDIR /app

# Copy only the Python packages and the virtual environment
COPY --from=builder /opt/venv /opt/venv

# Add the virtual environment to the PATH
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"

# Set the default command for the container
CMD ["/opt/venv/bin/black"]

# Run the test suite of the repository
RUN pytest

proxy_pool.dockerfile:
FROM python:3.6-alpine

MAINTAINER jhao104 <j_hao104@163.com>

WORKDIR /app

COPY ./requirements.txt .

# apk repository
RUN sed -i 's/dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/mirrors.ustc.edu.cn/g' /etc/apk/repositories

# timezone
RUN apk add -U tzdata && cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Shanghai /etc/localtime && apk del tzdata

# runtime environment
RUN apk add musl-dev gcc libxml2-dev libxslt-dev && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt && \
    apk del gcc musl-dev

COPY . ./

EXPOSE 5010

ENTRYPOINT [ "sh", "start.sh" ]

# Run the test suite
cmd ["python", "-m", "unittest", "discover", "-s", "test", "-v"]

FROM python:3.8

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Clone the repository
RUN git clone https://github.com/tqdm/tqdm.git

# Change the working directory to the cloned repo
WORKDIR /app/tqdm

# Install the package using pip
RUN pip install .

# Run the test suite
CMD ["python", "-m", "unittest"]

rich.dockerfile:
# Use an official Python runtime as a base image
FROM python:3.8

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the current directory contents into the container at /app
COPY . /app

# Install poetry and project dependencies
RUN curl -sSL https://install.python-poetry.org | python -
RUN cd /app && poetry install

# Run the test suite
CMD ["poetry", "run", "pytest"]

openpilot.dockerfile:
# Start with a base image that includes Python and Poetry
FROM python:3

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the poetry.lock and pyproject.toml files to the working directory
COPY poetry.lock pyproject.toml /app/

# Install Poetry and project dependencies
RUN pip install poetry && poetry install

# Clone the repository into the container
RUN git clone https://github.com/commaai/openpilot.git

# Set the working directory to the cloned repository
WORKDIR /app/openpilot

# Run the test suite to verify the installation
RUN pytest

open-interpreter.dockerfile:
# Use Python 3.8 image as base
FROM python:3.8

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the local code to the container's workspace
COPY . /app

# Install poetry
RUN curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/python-poetry/poetry/master/get-poetry.py | python

# Set environment variables for poetry
ENV PATH="$HOME/.poetry/bin:/app/.venv/bin:$PATH"
ENV POETRY_VIRTUALENVS_CREATE=false

# Install dependencies from poetry.lock
RUN poetry install

# Run the test suite
RUN poetry run pytest

black.dockerfile:
# Dockerfile for cloning the repository and setting up the working environment

# Use the official Python image as the base image
FROM python:3.12-slim AS builder

# Install required build tools to compile black and its dependencies
RUN apt update && apt install -y build-essential git python3-dev

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Clone the repository into the container
RUN git clone <repository_url> .

# Set up the virtual environment and install dependencies
RUN python -m venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
COPY ./requirements.txt /app
RUN . /opt/venv/bin/activate && pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip setuptools && pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

# Run the test suite of the repository
CMD ["/opt/venv/bin/pytest"]

FROM python:3.6-alpine

# Set the working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Install dependencies
RUN apk update \ 
    && apk add --no-cache git \ 
    && git clone <repo_url> . \ 
    && pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt \ 
    && apk del git

# Set timezone
RUN apk add -U tzdata && cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Shanghai /etc/localtime && apk del tzdata

# Runtime environment
RUN apk add musl-dev gcc libxml2-dev libxslt-dev 

# Copy the rest of the files
COPY . .

# Expose the port
EXPOSE 5010

# Set the entrypoint
ENTRYPOINT [ "sh", "start.sh" ]

# Run the test suite
RUN python -m unittest discover -s test -p 'test_*.py'
